<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
<title>MBTI test result</title>
<style type="text/css">
  #footer {
    /*position: fixed;*/
    bottom: 0;
    width: 100%;
  }
  /* Tablet Landscape */
  @media screen and (max-width: 1060px) {
    #primary { width:67%; }
    #secondary { width:30%; margin-left:3%;}  
  }

  /* Tabled Portrait */
  @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
      #primary { width:100%; }
      #secondary { width:100%; margin:0; border:none; }
  }
  @media (min-device-width:600px) {
      img[data-src-600px] {
          content: attr(data-src-600px, url);
      }
  }

  @media (min-device-width:800px) {
      img[data-src-800px] {
          content: attr(data-src-800px, url);
      }
  }
  html { font-size:100%; }
  @media (min-width: 640px) { body {font-size:1rem;} } 
  @media (min-width:960px) { body {font-size:1.2rem;} } 
  @media (min-width:1100px) { body {font-size:1.5rem;} }
  @media (min-width:1300px) { body {font-size:1.1rem;} } 
</style>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1,maximum-scale=1,user-scalable=no">
<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge,chrome=1">
<meta name="HandheldFriendly" content="true">
</head>

<body>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/0.98.2/css/materialize.min.css">

<div class="container" align="center">
<p align="center">
  Name : <b><%= user_name %></b> &nbsp; School : <b><%= school %></b> &nbsp;
</p>
<p align="center">
  Branch : <b><%= branch %></b> &nbsp; Employee ID : <b><%= employee_id %></b> &nbsp; Designation : <b><%= designation %></b>
</p>
   

   <div class="row" id="resCard" align="center">
     <div class="col s12 m6 offset-m3">
        <div class="card-panel teal">
          <span horizontal-align="center" class="white-text">
            <h5>Your Personality Type is</h5>
            <h2 text-align="center"> <%= my_result %> </h2>
            
            <% if first_char == 'E' %>
              ( Extraversion, &nbsp;
            <% else %>
              ( Introversion, &nbsp;
            <% end %>

            <% if second_char == 'S' %>
              Sensing, &nbsp;
            <% else %>
              Intuition, &nbsp;
            <% end %>

            <% if third_char == 'T' %>
              Thinking, &nbsp;
            <% else %>
              Feeling, &nbsp;
            <% end %>

            <% if fourth_char == 'J' %>
              Judging )
            <% else %>
              Perceiving )
            <% end %>
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
  </div>

    <% if first_char == 'E' %>
      <blockquote>
        <b>Extraversion</b> refers to the act or state of being energized by the world outside the self. Extraverts enjoy socializing and tend to be more enthusiastic, assertive, talkative and animated. They enjoy time spent with more people and find it less rewarding to spend time alone.
      </blockquote>
    <% else %>
      <blockquote>
        <b>Introversion</b> refers to the state of being predominately concerned with one’s inner world. Introverts prefer self-reflection to social interactions. They also prefer to observe before participating in an activity. Introverts tend to be more quiet, peaceful and reserved.
      </blockquote>
    <% end %>

    <% if second_char == 'S' %>
      <blockquote>
        <b>Sensing</b> refers to processing data through the five senses. Sensing people focus on the present and prefer to learn by doing rather than thinking it through. they are more recognized by the practical use of an object/idea rather than the memory behind it.
      </blockquote>
    <% else %>
      <blockquote>
        <b>Intuition</b> refers to how people process data. Intuitive people are keener to the meaning and patterns behind information. Intuitive people are more focused on how the present would affect the future. They are ready to grasp different possibilities and abstract concepts.
      </blockquote>
    <% end %>

    <% if third_char == 'T' %>
      <blockquote>
        <b>Thinking</b> refers to how people make decisions. Thinking people are objective and base their decision on hard logic and facts. They tend to analyze the pros and cons of a situation and notice inconsistencies. They prefer to be task-oriented and fair.
      </blockquote>
    <% else %>
      <blockquote>
        <b>Feeling</b> people are more subjective. They base their decisions on principles and personal values. When making decisions, they consider other people’s feelings and take it in account. It is in their best mind to maintain harmony among a group. 
      </blockquote>
    <% end %>

    <% if fourth_char == 'J' %>
      <blockquote>
        <b>Judging</b> refers to how people outwardly display themselves when making descions. Judging people have a tendency to be organized and prompt. They like order prefer outlined schedules to working extemporaneously. 
      </blockquote>
    <% else %>
      <blockquote>
        <b>Perceiving</b> people prefer flexibility and their life with spontaneity. They dislike structure and prefer to adapt to new situations rather than plan for it. They tend to be open to new options and experiences. 
      </blockquote>
    <% end %>


  <br>
  <a href="/"><h5>Take Test Again</h5></a>
</div>
